{"abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GSignalGroup"},{"type":"text","text":" manages a collection of signals on a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GObject"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"SignalGroupRef","kind":"identifier"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"overview","text":"Overview","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"code":"GSignalGroup","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" simplifies the process of connecting  many signals to a "},{"code":"GObject","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"as a group. As such there is no API to disconnect a signal from the group.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"In particular, this allows you to:","type":"text"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Change the target instance, which automatically causes disconnection"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"of the signals from the old instance and connecting to the new instance."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Block and unblock signals as a group"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Ensuring that blocked state transfers across target instances.","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"One place you might want to use such a structure is with "},{"code":"GtkTextView","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GtkTextBuffer"},{"text":". Often times, you’ll need to connect to many signals on","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GtkTextBuffer"},{"type":"text","text":" from a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GtkTextView"},{"type":"text","text":" subclass. This